  <title>
    <phrase lang="en">Arbitrary Rotation</phrase>
    <phrase lang="de">Beliebig drehen</phrase>
    <phrase lang="fr">Rotation arbitraire</phrase>
    <phrase lang="no">Valfri rotasjon</phrase>
    <phrase lang="zh_CN">任意旋转</phrase>
  </title>

  <indexterm lang="en">
    <primary>Layer</primary>
    <secondary>Transform layer</secondary>
    <tertiary>Rotation</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang="en">
    <primary>Arbitrary Rotation</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <indexterm lang="de">
    <primary>Ebene</primary>
    <secondary>drehen</secondary>
  </indexterm>

  <indexterm lang="fr">
    <primary>Calque</primary>
    <secondary>Transformer le calque</secondary>
    <tertiary>Rotation</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang="fr">
    <primary>Rotation arbitraire</primary>
  </indexterm>
  
  <indexterm lang="no">
    <primary>Lagmenyen</primary>
    <secondary>Transformer</secondary>
    <tertiary>Valfri rotasjon</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang="no">
    <primary>Transformer</primary>
    <secondary>Valfri rotasjon</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm lang="no">
    <primary>Rotére lag</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <para lang="en">
    The <guimenuitem>Arbitrary Rotation</guimenuitem> command rotates a
    layer by a specified angle. It is an alternate way of accessing the
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-rotate">Rotate tool</link>. See the section
    about that tool for more information.
  </para>
  <para lang="de">
    Mit diesem Kommando können Sie eine Ebene um einen beliebigen Winkel drehen.
    Hierzu verwendet <acronym>GIMP</acronym> das Werkzeug
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-rotate">Drehen</link>.
  </para>
  <para lang="fr">
    C'est une autre manière d'activer l'outil
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-rotate">Rotation</link>.
  </para>
  <para lang="no">
    Kommandoen <guimenuitem>Valfri rotasjon</guimenuitem> roterer det
    aktive laget ein valfri vinkel, og er ein annan måte å få tilgang til <!--PENDING:no
    <link linkend="gimp-tool-rotate"-->Rotasjonsverktøyet<!--/link--> på. Du finn
    også fyldigare informasjon under beskrivinga av dette verktøyet.
  </para>

